{
  "texts": [
    "Structural images were recorded using an MPRAGE [56] T1 protocol with 1 mm isotropic resolution and F OV = 256 × 256 mm.Stimuli were presented using MATLAB (The Mathworks Inc., Natick, MA, USA) with the Psychophysics Toolbox [57] and delivered through an Optoacoustics (Optoacoustics Ltd, Or Yehuda, Israel) amplifier and headphones equipped with active noise-cancellation.",
    "Loudness was adjusted independently for each participant to a comfortable level before starting data acquisition.",
    "Data preprocessingData was preprocessed using fMRIPrep 23.2.2 [58,59], which is based on Nipype 1.8.6 [60,61].The T1w image was corrected for intensity non-uniformity (INU) with N4BiasFieldCorrection [62], distributed with ANTs 2.5.0 [63], and used as T1w-reference throughout the workflow.",
    "The T1w-reference was then skull-stripped with ANTs (version 2.5.0), using OASIS30ANTs as target template.",
    "Brain tissue segmentation of cerebrospinal fluid (CSF), white-matter (WM) and gray-matter (GM) was performed on the brain-extracted T1w using fast (FSL) [64]."
  ]
}